## Example 3 â€” Combine Cubes and Squares

Factor:

`64x^6 - y^6`

This can be viewed as a difference of squares first:

`64x^6 - y^6 = (8x^3)^2 - (y^3)^2`

`= (8x^3 + y^3)(8x^3 - y^3)`

Now factor each expression as cubes:

`= [(2x)^3 + y^3][(2x)^3 - y^3]`

`= (2x + y)(4x^2 - 2xy + y^2)(2x - y)(4x^2 + 2xy + y^2)`

